óŸOarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/book/standard_library.mdŸ@d13daf0bdfb6d25ccb04a347e9b4b6be8c340f2bb0327cef8bae52648a1af005•prev:ëæImporting the Standard Library⁄îThe Standard Library modules and submodules are imported with the 
[link: /commands/docs/use.md] ``use``
 command, just as any other module. See 
[link: ./modules/using_modules.md] Using Modules
 for more information.
While working at the commandline, it can be convenient to load the entire standard library using:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
use std *

```
However, this form should be avoided in custom commands and scripts since it has the longest load time.
::: important Optimal Startup when Using the Standard Library

See the 
[link: #optimal-startup] notes below
 on how to ensure that your configuration isn't loading the entire Standard Library.

:::
íêê⁄œTitle: prev:
Path: Importing the Standard Library
Content:
The Standard Library modules and submodules are imported with the 
[link: /commands/docs/use.md] ``use``
 command, just as any other module. See 
[link: ./modules/using_modules.md] Using Modules
 for more information.
While working at the commandline, it can be convenient to load the entire standard library using:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
use std *

```
However, this form should be avoided in custom commands and scripts since it has the longest load time.
::: important Optimal Startup when Using the Standard Library

See the 
[link: #optimal-startup] notes below
 on how to ensure that your configuration isn't loading the entire Standard Library.

:::
