óŸOarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/book/standard_library.mdŸ@c249322224abd83f4ff02b5855a99eec20b7e638bd4ee947f1b56fca27c0fa73•prev:ëØOptimal Startup⁄ÃIf Nushell's startup time is important to your workflow, review your 
[link: [./configuration.md]] startup configuration
 in 
``config.nu``
, 
``env.nu``
, and potentially others for inefficient use of the standard library. The following command should identify any problem areas:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
view files
| enumerate | flatten
| where filename !~ '^std'
| where filename !~ '^entry'
| where {|file|
    (view span $file.start $file.end) =~ 'use\W+std[^\/]'
  }

```
Edit those files to use the recommended syntax in the 
[link: #importing-submodules] Importing Submodules
 section above.
::: note

If a Nushell library (e.g., from 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts] the 
``nu_scripts``
 repository
), example, or doc is using this syntax, please report it via an issue or PR. These will be updated over time after Nushell 0.99.0 is released.
If a third-party module is using this syntax, please report it to the author/maintainers to update.

:::
íêê⁄¯Title: prev:
Path: Optimal Startup
Content:
If Nushell's startup time is important to your workflow, review your 
[link: [./configuration.md]] startup configuration
 in 
``config.nu``
, 
``env.nu``
, and potentially others for inefficient use of the standard library. The following command should identify any problem areas:
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
view files
| enumerate | flatten
| where filename !~ '^std'
| where filename !~ '^entry'
| where {|file|
    (view span $file.start $file.end) =~ 'use\W+std[^\/]'
  }

```
Edit those files to use the recommended syntax in the 
[link: #importing-submodules] Importing Submodules
 section above.
::: note

If a Nushell library (e.g., from 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nu_scripts] the 
``nu_scripts``
 repository
), example, or doc is using this syntax, please report it via an issue or PR. These will be updated over time after Nushell 0.99.0 is released.
If a third-party module is using this syntax, please report it to the author/maintainers to update.

:::
